  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Comprehensive vocational training increasing economic activity (Sierra Leone)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Youth unemployment is a major problem in Sierra Leone. Not only does it make life very difficult for young people themselves who have no possibility of making their own living, but having young people hanging around with nothing to do also increases the risks of them engaging in negative activities and violence. This project will fight unemployment head-on by providing some of the worst-off young people with training and apprenticeships. The result of the project will be that young people either get jobs or become self-employed. That means they and their families will have a better standard of living, and that local businesses and the local economy will thrive. There should also be less chance of young people becoming frustrated and getting involved in violence.</narrative>
  </description>
